      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Allene, H<sub>2</sub>C<span data-math=\"\\text{=}\"></span>C<span data-math=\"\\text{=}\"></span>CH<sub>2</sub>, has two adjacent double bonds. Draw a picture showing the orbitals involved in the <i>σ</i> and <i>π</i> bonds of allene. Is the central carbon atom <i>sp</i><sup>2</sup>- or <i>sp</i>-hybridized? What about the hybridization of the terminal carbons? What shape do you predict for allene?</p>",
